Here is an easy way to understand the difference between getElementById, getElementsByClassName, 
and querySelector / querySelectorAll:

getElementById used when you want just one element using its unique ID.
getElementsByClassName used when you want multiple elements that share the same class name.
querySelector used when you want one element that matches a CSS selector.
querySelectorAll  used when you want all elements that match a CSS selector.

